device test program for files.
write file to device (e.g. hard disk) with dummy content to show device speed.
note:
can be also used to
- test maximum file size.
- fill up device space.

todo:
1. translate code messages to english.
2. improve elapsed time measure (presently 1 second accuracy).

usage:
  #Linux or cygwin
  echo 64 | fwrite #write a file of 64MB and show elapsed time
  mfwrite.sh 0 9 256 #write 10 files of 256MB

  #Windows (enter 64 by hand)
  cd C:\temp
  fwrite.exe

  #Linux
  cd /dev/shm
  mfwrite.sh 0 9 64 #write 10 files of 64MB

